{"id": "EUVD-2022-55381", "enisaUuid": "3b1cb792-bb35-3567-a4cd-d492fd3df4df", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nASoC: SOF: ipc3-topology: Prevent double freeing of ipc_control_data via load_bytes\n\nWe have sanity checks for byte controls and if any of the fail the locally\nallocated scontrol->ipc_control_data is freed up, but not set to NULL.\n\nOn a rollback path of the error the higher level code will also try to free\nthe scontrol->ipc_control_data which will eventually going to lead to\nmemory corruption as double freeing memory is not a good thing.", "datePublished": "2025-06-18T12:30:49", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-18T18:32:45", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8463986b54295e6b65ddf2b7c65627d01ce7643b", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/c2eddfcafcffaf1b9245ea0dde9143bbfb47d5d1", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/d5bd47f3ca124058a8e87eae4508afeda2132611", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50115"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50115"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "1d65fd8f-88e0-3515-b345-2020be9aa083", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "273d4a26-2298-3e31-8abd-bcccefb732c1", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.19.2"}, {"id": "316addce-70b1-39f1-beb1-850c691ff37b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "b5cee8feb1d482a9d07b677f4f2f9565bacda53e <c2eddfcafcffaf1b9245ea0dde9143bbfb47d5d1"}, {"id": "667ced91-c463-3997-84d6-6377744978c1", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.0"}, {"id": "95e67596-9932-3b67-8184-49a3a9e8f22c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.18.18"}, {"id": "db553a2c-6e11-30e4-ac9d-cfaedc0e1490", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "b5cee8feb1d482a9d07b677f4f2f9565bacda53e <8463986b54295e6b65ddf2b7c65627d01ce7643b"}, {"id": "df2390a7-79df-3680-b578-a183fc20175a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_versio